Class LinkNetworkSearchNode

java.lang.Object

      com.i2group.apollo.networksearchservice.transport.LinkNetworkSearchNode

public final class LinkNetworkSearchNode
extends NetworkSearchNode

A kind of NetworkSearchNode that defines criteria that a Link must match in order to appear in network search results.

Since:
4.0

LinkNetworkSearchNode

public LinkNetworkSearchNode(String nodeId,
                             SearchNode searchNode,
                             boolean isOutputEnabled,
                             List<String> disabledFilterInfoIds,
                             String fromNodeId,
                             String toNodeId)
Constructs a new LinkNetworkSearchNode, initializing all mandatory fields.

Parameters:
nodeId - A String containing an identifier for this LinkNetworkSearchNode that must be unique within the network of nodes.
searchNode - The SearchNode that this LinkNetworkSearchNode contains.
isOutputEnabled - true if Links that matched this NetworkSearchNode should be included in the network search results; false otherwise.
disabledFilterInfoIds - Strings identifying FilterInfos within the SearchNode that will not be applied when the network search involving this LinkNetworkSearchNode takes place.
fromNodeId - A String containing the identifier of the EntityNetworkSearchNode that determines which Entitys can appear at the "from" end of Links that match this LinkNetworkSearchNode.
toNodeId - A String containing the identifier of the EntityNetworkSearchNode that determines which Entitys can appear at the "to" end of Links that match this LinkNetworkSearchNode.
